          <text>
                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p rend="indent(9)">
                                        <placeName>London</placeName>
                                        <date>29th Novr 5611</date>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(10)">
                                        <placeName>6 Great Alie St. Goodman's fields</placeName>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(8)">
                                        <add>כ"ד כסלו ש' לא תיר"א מהם</add>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">Revd &amp; Dear Sir/</p>
                              <p rend="indent(4)">I am quite ashamed of my conduct towards<lb/> you
                                        and do confess <add>בושתי וגם נכלמתי</add> for not replying
                                        to your last communication<lb/> to me, as well as for the
                                        review of the "way of Faith" and for your friendly
                                        expressions<lb/> I feel indebted to you, but sufficient is
                                        to express my sorrow, and that an alarming<lb/> complaint
                                        was my preventative for so doing to a man of that high
                                        esteem, regard,<lb/> &amp; veneration I hold for your high
                                        talents and true learning (<add>חטאתי</add>), ever since I
                                        first had<lb/> the satisfaction of perusing your scientific
                                        writings, but since <add>מוצאי כפור</add>
                                        <date>5610</date> I was attacked<lb/> with a severe cold
                                        which gradually brought on an attack in the wind-pipe &amp;
                                        which<lb/> actually despaired me causing some alarm till
                                        very lately which with care &amp; attention<lb/> blessed be
                                        God am quite recover'd, however for the present we must
                                        leave further details, it is to<lb/> me a more important
                                        subject on which I address you now, With truly painful
                                        sorrows<lb/> I have seen in the Jewish Chronicle the place
                                        of <add>חזן</add> vacant advertising for one, I must<lb/>
                                        solemnly declare to you that I know nothing of the matter in
                                        any way whatever,</p>
                              <p rend="align center">but some time since <sic>learnt</sic> that
                                        there were some trifling</p>
                              <p rend="align center">differences but matters would be arranged which
                                        gave</p>
                              <p rend="align center">me much gratification; of course this newly
                                        advertisement astonished</p>
                              <p>me, now dear sir it has ever been with me a maxim <add>אלא ליבכם
                                                  בתחום שאינו שלי</add> but in the present<lb/> case
                                        I must, it is most sacred with me <add>איש את רעהו יעזרו
                                                  ולאחיו יאמר חזק</add> and as having been for a
                                        number<lb/> of years <add>אב בית דין ומ"ז</add> of the first
                                        Portuguese Congregation in <placeName>Europe</placeName>,
                                        also recognized by all<lb/> universities
                                                  <placeName>Italy</placeName>,
                                                  <placeName>Germany</placeName>,
                                                  <placeName>Turkey</placeName>, <placeName>Holy
                                                  land</placeName>, as <add>מוחזק לבר אוריין ובר
                                                  אבהן ומורה בישראל</add>,<lb/> and, as the
                                        descendant of that family which for the last 500 years have
                                        been I consider<lb/> myself in duty bound to interfere &amp;
                                        settle matters in your favour, after you have served<lb/>
                                        them so many years sown the seed of knowledge &amp; wisdom,
                                        such an action ought not<lb/> to be done to a great man of
                                        your valuable erudition, would my health permit I<lb/> would
                                        most willingly cross the <placeName>Great Sea</placeName> to
                                        serve you &amp; put them to rights <del>and</del><lb/>
                                        <sic>shewing</sic> them <add>and, as the descendant of that
                                                  family which for the last 500 years have been I
                                                  consider רבני הדור</add> pray without any loss of
                                        time as a brother Israelite, &amp; friend in the<lb/> field
                                        of literature reply to my letter, and in the greatest
                                        confidence let me know how I can<lb/> serve you and to be of
                                        use to you, I beg that you, &amp; they, will give in a
                                        little in the existing differences,</p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p>I have laid before me many important cases from all parts to decide
                                        upon <add>כי כן לא יעשה בישראל</add><lb/> and I am not
                                        fearful that this will also be one I may succeed <add>לפשר
                                                  דבר ולתווך השלום</add>, they may advertise here
                                        but<lb/> they <del>will</del> can only find as
                                                  <persName>Leeser's</persName> old shoes, <hi
                                                  rend="underline">all I say is in confidence</hi>.
                                        You may make use of my<lb/> name in any way it can be of use
                                        to you. You may mention to a <persName>Mr A: Hart</persName>
                                        &amp; another<lb/> gent<hi rend="sup">n</hi>. whom I have
                                        seen that application must be made to them, not to be in
                                        such a hurry<lb/> and to allow me to address them a truly
                                        pastoral letter in your favour, as a true disciple<lb/> of
                                                  <persName>Aaron</persName>
                                        <add>בע"ה</add> and as the son and Disciple of that immortal
                                        father acknowledged<lb/> by all in 4 parts of the globe
                                                  <add>אוהב שלום ורודף שלום</add>. I am determined
                                        to serve you &amp; seek this important<lb/> blessing <add>א'
                                                  מיחידי וגדולי הדור הישן</add> and not to be
                                        allowed for the sake of a few tempers to <sic>supress</sic>
                                        it. Favour me<lb/> with an immediate answer &amp; trust you
                                        will hearken unto my voice do not abandon it,<lb/> wishing
                                        you with all my heart every blessing <add>שלום</add> with
                                        all esteem<lb/> I am Revd. &amp; Dear Sir</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">Yours very faithfully</p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">
                                        <persName role="author">David Meldola</persName>
                              </p>
                              <p>It is peace and peace only I seek for,<lb/> trusting that as a
                                                  gent<hi rend="sup">n</hi>. you will keep a secret
                                        such,<lb/> terms which I wrote you confidentially; our friend<lb/>
                                        <persName>Hasone Pisa's</persName> best respects to you
                                        &amp; shall be happy to hear from you <add>וכל אשר אתה עושה
                                                  ה' מצליח</add></p>
                              <p>
                                        <addressee>Revd. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">
                                        <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
                              </p>
